<section class="faq-section rv">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl">
    <h2 class="faq-heading">
      Frequently Asked <span class="faq-accent">Questions</span>
    </h2>

    <div class="faq-list" data-stagger>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">What types of assets can you help unblock?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Securities held in Euroclear, Clearstream and NSD accounts, funds on Type "C" accounts, shares in foreign entities, bank deposits and other financial instruments subject to sanctions-related restrictions.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">Which jurisdictions do you cover?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Russia, Cyprus, Belgium, Luxembourg, France, Switzerland, the United Kingdom, Spain, Turkey, Romania, Latvia, Moldova, BVI, Panama, Seychelles and the UAE. The network of local partners extends to additional jurisdictions as needed.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">How long does the licensing process typically take?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Timelines vary by jurisdiction and the nature of the assets. Individual licenses from Euroclear or Clearstream usually take 3 to 9 months. We provide a realistic timeline estimate after reviewing your specific situation.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">Is the initial consultation confidential?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Yes. All communications are subject to attorney-client privilege from the first contact. No information is shared with third parties without explicit written consent.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">What information do I need to provide for an initial assessment?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">A general description of the asset structure, the jurisdictions involved, and the nature of the issue you are facing. Specific documents can be discussed during the first consultation.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">Do you work with corporate clients or only individuals?</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Both. We advise private investors, entrepreneurs, family offices and corporate groups on cross-border structuring, tax optimization and regulatory matters.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-section {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .faq-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .faq-accent {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(43, 76, 126, 0.12);
  }
  .faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(43, 76, 126, 0.12);
  }

  .faq-question {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text);
    padding: 1.4rem 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }
  .faq-question::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .faq-question::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-left: 1rem;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item[open] .faq-question::after {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  .faq-question:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .faq-answer {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding: 0 0 1.4rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .faq-section { padding: 3.5rem 0; }
    .faq-question { font-size: 1rem; padding: 1.2rem 0; }
  }
</style>

